Right — content negotiation on the same URL, not a separate `/sse` path. That's already half-built in the router:

```typescript
// src/index.ts lines 86-111
if (method === "GET" && path === "/") {
  // ...
  if (isSSERequest(request)) {
    return await handleTodaySSE(env, auth.userId, tz);
  }
  // else return HTML shell
}
```

So the design stays simpler:

- `GET /` with `Accept: text/html` → Worker returns HTML shell
- `GET /` with `Accept: text/event-stream` → Worker proxies to DO, which holds the stream and projects state
- Same for `/progress`, `/program`, `/routine/:id` — same URL, content negotiation picks the channel

The HTML shell includes Datastar attributes that automatically open the SSE connection to the same URL. No separate `/sse` endpoint needed. This is already the pattern in the router — it just needs to proxy to the DO instead of building a static response.

Does the revised Section 1 look right?

